rcise missing branch\\\" by asserting that it ends with closure1Missing. The NoClassDefFoundError thrown in class$ catches ClassNotFoundException and then raises a NoClassDefFoundError with the full binary class name. That's good. I also need to consider that `RestAssuredHttpBuilderGroovyHelper.flattenToString` might not execute the closure because it uses a generated helper delegate, but the behavioral assertion works fine. The active call site is indeed the direct resolver, and the user asked specifically about the active class.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented focused coverage for the active Rest Assured dynamic-access class.\n\nAdded:\n- `tests/src/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/5.5.0/src/test/java/io_rest_assured/rest_assured/RestAssuredHttpBuilderGroovyHelperInner_flattenToString_closure1Test.java`\n  - Dedicated one-to-one test for `RestAssuredHttpBuilderGroovyHelper$_flattenToString_closure1`\n  - Exercises the compiler-generated `class$` resolver for:\n    - the active closure class\n    - a JDK runtime class\n    - a missing class branch\n  - Includes a public API behavior assertion for `flattenToString`\n\n- `tests/src/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/5.5.0/src/test/java/io/restassured/internal/RestAssuredHttpBuilderGroovyHelperFlattenToStringClosure1Access.java`\n  - Small package helper to invoke the Groovy synthetic `class$` method through `MethodHandles`, matching existing test patterns.\n\nI did not run or compile tests, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_00c9c94b8643caf7016a019c7713b48194ac53ce31e76cd038\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 707, "output": 737, "cacheRead": 48640, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 50084, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1778490474373, "responseId": "resp_00c9c94b8643caf7016a019c6b593c8194bf31b6bd9ac4ae6a"}}
